First off, I am a Bartender/waitress. Yes, it IS my job to get you food and beer. That said, I would like to share with you just exactly what I earn for doing that job. A whooping $2.13 an hour. Now, If everybody who came in to my bar figured it was my job to serve them and didnt think they needed to tip for my time and energy, well, I wouldnt have enough money per month to pay for EQ let alone pay any real bills. If everybody thought like this, every restraunt would be serve your self, because one of the ways restraunts are able to stay open and serve good food at a decent price, is the fact that most of their employees work for almost nothing.<br>
