 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umaeri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maeri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 469<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/2/02 6:17:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3371.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: donations</span><hr size=1> Protocol for tipping vary greatly around the world. Just looked up US minimum wage laws, and I see that the minimum wage is $5.15/hr, unless the employee is getting tips, in which case it reduces to $2.13/hr on the understanding that they get the difference in tips. Bleagh! In countries that don't give employers of bar and wait staff that loophole, there's not as much expectation that a tip will be provided. I'll give a tip in a restaurant only if I thought the service was particularly good. In a quick search for waitressing jobs here in Australia, the first one I found that mentioned a rate of pay was $AUD14/hr. (Call it $US7/hr) Minimum wage in the UK is £4.20 an hour. Ooo.. found a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.exp.ie/advice/mercer.html">list of minimum wages</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> around the world. Probably worth cross-referencing that with <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.finfacts.com/costofliving.htm">costs of living</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. And don't take up a minimum wage job in Moscow. <p>----------------------------------<br>
[59 Troubadour]
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78662">Maeri</a>
&lt;Anlah'Shok&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usaraquael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saraquael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 346<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/2/02 10:27:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3371.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: donations</span><hr size=1> As someone who has taken donations both in game (as a druid) and in real life (as an artist), I have to say that not all people who mention donations expect something. The term &quot;donation&quot; has pretty much always been misused. By definition, it's strictly voluntary, yet these days a lot of people mean it's required.<br>
<br>
In grade school, I got in trouble for not donating to the poor box (I'm 7 years old... where the hell am I gonna get money from?)<br>
<br>
At my parent's church, they try and encourage the people there to donate at least 10% of their wages to the church.<br>
<br>
That's crap. If someone wants to donate, they decide 2 things.<br>
<br>
1. Yes or no.<br>
2. How much.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, this is one of those things that goes round and round with no actual resolution. <br>
<br>
Now, on the subject of tipping. If I get the food myself, I usually don't tip (except for change... I hate change, but that doesn't really count). So basically, I don't pay much attention to the tip jars at the register. However, if I the food is brought to me, then I always tip at least the customary 15%. If the server is someone who has served me a few times in the past before, then I tip a little more. If they have to deal with assholes at another table that I can see, then I usually try and tip a little more as well. Granted, all this goes out the window if the service sucks (never had that happened though). <p><p><center><a href=http://www.saraquael.com><img src=http://www.saraquael.com/Images/signature2002.jpg></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarayalebon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Araya LeBon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 260<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/3/02 12:05:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3371.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: donations</span><hr size=1> "? Donation's are just like those damn little Tip Jars that coffee stores put out! The one's that scream, "I'm here and if you don't put a dollar in there you'll look like a cheap ass." --- Why the hell should I tip someone for serving me coffee?! That's your job!! No one's pay's me tip's to do my job! RAWR! :-P "<br>
<br>
