<br>
  That's a good point. The same problem exists on the people who demand, request, or ask nicely for ports. Sometimes they don't even mention if they plan to pay. Other times it's paying, donation, or my favorite, &quot;paying well&quot;. (Paying well could be 5pp or 200pp. If you like bad gambles, go for it.) Generally you can get away with 10pp as the minimum, but a lot of greedier porters will scoff at less than 100pp. <br>
<br>
  Personally, these days I just don't bother to port much. High pp amounts only let me know how serious the person is in their request; I don't need money because I don't have quite enough item desire or hope to try buying much. I do accept money as proof that my services are worth something. <br>
<br>
  You should just counter with your port request and name a figure. If someone responds, fine, if not you can raise your price or keep running. In fact, most of my alts never buy teleports. My warrior has run, unsowed, from Misty Thicket (original bind point) to Great Divide on CR. He hates that Iceclad boat and Iceclad in general. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usejaltraurig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sejal Traurig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/5/02 10:28:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3371.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Because some people just don't understand English</span><hr size=1> Frankly, I don't understand what Guildon is complaining about.<br>
<br>
Casting X for donations means just exactly that. Donate. Get the offered spell cast. Don't donate, you get nothing. That is, as near as I can tell, as plain English as it can get. Donate. Get something. Don't Donate. Get nothing. Easy. Simple. Clear.<br>
<br>
What Guildon is REALLY saying is: &quot;I'm a cheap bastard that wants something for nothing. No I'm not going to give you anything for your time. Buff/Port me and appreciate the fact that you got to be nice to me. Maybe I'll let you buff/port me again later.&quot;<br>
<br>
See, I cast C3 for donations quite frequently. I've been given as much as 260 plat for a single person. I've also accepted and cast for as little as 3 plat for a person. Price isn't the issue when it comes to a donation. Someone said something like 'people who use the word donation instead of setting a price just don't want to sound like port whores'.. Not so in my case. There is one reason and one reason alone that I do not set a price. Allow me to explain.<br>
<br>
When someone asks me &quot;How much for C3?&quot; I reply (And yes.. I type it out every time because its too damned long for a hotkey) &quot;I have no set price. Donate what you feel it is worth to you to get a Clarity 3 with 25 int and 25 wis that also increases your mana pool by 250 and lasts for 2.5 hours.&quot; (Lucky for me I type fast, so I can usually get one sent before the next person asks me the same question).. So I say Donation NOT because I want to avoid sounding like a buff whore.. But because, plain and simple, its WORTH more to some people than it is to others.. <br>
<br>
People have said &quot;This is all I have with me.. Is that enough?&quot; The ONLY times I have EVER said &quot;No, you need to get more&quot; was when an Epic Cleric tried giving me 130 SILVER. I turned down the silver.. But the cleric STILL GOT C3.. I said &quot;If thats all you can afford, you need it more than I do&quot;<br>
<br>
Another time I turned down someone who asked me to C3 him and gave me 20 plat.. Then all of a sudden a bunch more people from the same guild as him showed up. I invited him to join my group because I could see what was coming.. He donated for HIM.. But wanted C3 for his entire group.. Well, I'm willing to cast on the guy because he donated, but he refused to join my group.. He says &quot;I donated for the entire group.. Can you hurry it up? We are on our way to a raid.&quot;<br>
<br>
Now keep in mind, when he sent me a tell asking if I could C3 &quot;HIM&quot; (He said nothing about his entire group) I had around 15 seconds to finish camping out.. So.. I cancelled the camp and waited.. And waited.. And waited.. for him to get there (See, he wasn't even in the same ZONE yet) While I was waiting I /ooc'ed &quot;Casting C3 for donations at the Kunark Scion..&quot; I manged to make a little plat while waiting on the guy..<br>
<br>
So I gave the guy his money back and he went on his way (I assume to the raid he was talking about) all pissed off at me because I wouldn't C3 his entire group for 20 plat after having been made to wait as long as I was to do HIM a favor.<br>
<br>
So spare me the English Language speech.. Saying &quot;I'll do something in return for something else&quot; (I.E. an exchange of cash) is pretty plain. In ANY language.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=3371.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showPrevMessage?topicID=3371.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showNextMessage?topicID=3371.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3371.topic&index=34><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.emailToFriend?topicID=3371.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.threadControl?topicID=3371.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3371.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3371.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub4.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select n